This line made me go between it and inspecting the ssl3_record_st structure carefully, since the way it was written looked like a flexible array member:<p><pre><code>    unsigned char *p = &s->s3->rrec.data[0], *pl;
</code></pre>
I think it would be better written as:<p><pre><code>    unsigned char *p = s->s3->rrec.data, *pl;
</code></pre>
to make it clearer that data is a pointer within the structure.
